# Adapt Clone Project Rules

## Project Overview
AI-powered business intelligence tool connecting to Notion, Google Drive, Airtable, and GitHub.

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 14 (App Router)
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
- Prisma + PostgreSQL
- NextAuth.js
- OpenAI GPT-4o

## Coding Standards

### TypeScript
- Use strict TypeScript with proper type annotations
- Define interfaces for all data structures
- Avoid `any` type - use `unknown` if truly dynamic

### React/Next.js
- Use Server Components by default, Client Components only when needed
- Use `"use client"` directive explicitly when required
- Prefer server actions for form submissions
- Use Next.js Image component for images

### Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes
- Use shadcn/ui components as the base
- Follow mobile-first responsive design
- Use CSS variables for theming

### API Routes
- Validate all inputs
- Return consistent error responses
- Use proper HTTP status codes
- Implement proper error handling

### Security
- Never log sensitive data (tokens, passwords)
- Always encrypt tokens at rest
- Use environment variables for secrets
- Validate user sessions on protected routes

## File Structure
```
src/
├── app/                 # Next.js App Router pages
├── components/          # React components
│   ├── ui/             # shadcn/ui components
│   └── features/       # Feature-specific components
├── lib/                # Utilities and helpers
├── services/           # Business logic and API services
└── types/              # TypeScript type definitions
```

